- The carboxylic acid group contributes to an increased melting point through the potential for intermolecular hydrogen bonding. However, since cinnamic acid already has this group, we do not make an additional adjustment for it here. 
The effects of added substituent groups are combined and added to the base value of cinnamic acid to predict the melting point of 5-bromo-2-fluorocinnamic acid.
